	<key>readme</key>
	<string>Fli Flights — Alfred Workflow

Type "flyhelp" in Alfred to browse the full interactive guide.

KEYWORDS
────────
  flights ORIGIN DEST MM-DD [options]
      Search flights on a specific date.
      ↵ copies details  |  ⌘↵ opens Google Flights  |  ⇧⌘↵ add to Calendar

  flydates ORIGIN DEST [options]
      Find the cheapest travel dates.
      ↵ opens Google Flights  |  ⌘↵ copies details

  nsflt ORIGIN DEST [options]
      Nonstop flights today (date + stops auto-set).
      ↵ copies details  |  ⌘↵ opens Google Flights  |  ⇧⌘↵ add to Calendar

  nstom ORIGIN DEST [options]
      Nonstop flights tomorrow (date + stops auto-set).
      ↵ copies details  |  ⌘↵ opens Google Flights  |  ⇧⌘↵ add to Calendar

  flyhelp [filter]
      Browse all commands, options, and examples.

DATES — no year needed
──────────────────────
  Just type MM-DD (e.g. 05-15). The current year is
  assumed; if that date already passed it rolls to next year.
  Full YYYY-MM-DD still works too.

OPTIONS (flights)
─────────────────
  --class    ECONOMY | PREMIUM_ECONOMY | BUSINESS | FIRST
  --stops    ANY | NON_STOP | ONE_STOP
  --sort     CHEAPEST | DURATION | DEPARTURE_TIME | ARRIVAL_TIME
  --return   MM-DD   (round-trip)
  --time     6-20    (departure window, 24h)
  --airlines BA AA   (IATA codes)

OPTIONS (flydates)
──────────────────
  --from MM-DD --to MM-DD   (date range)
  --round                   (round-trip)
  --duration 5              (trip length in days)
  --friday --saturday       (day filters, combine any)
  --class / --stops         (same as flights)

Powered by https://github.com/punitarani/fli</string>
